===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|crudan|crūdan|lang=ang}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|kruien|lang=nl}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive}} To [[push]], to [[press]], to [[shove]].
# {{context|transitive}} To  press or [[drive]] together; to [[mass]] together.
# {{context|transitive}} To [[fill]] by pressing or thronging together; hence, to encumber by [[excess]] of numbers or quantity.
# {{context|transitive}} To press by [[solicitation]]; to [[urge]]; to dun; hence, to treat [[discourteously]] or [[unreasonably]].
# {{context|nautical}} To approach another [[ship]] too closely when it has [[right of way]]
# {{context|intransitive}} To press together or [[collect]] in numbers; to [[swarm]]; to [[throng]]
# {{context|intransitive}} To urge or press forward; to force one's self; as, a man crowds into a room
# {{context|nautical}} (''of a square-rigged ship'') {{transitive}} To carry excessive sail

